ification program for recovery residence administrators and residences. Read more. Personal Stories: The Impact of Treatment Have you ever wondered what treatment is like? The Substance Abuse and Mental Health Program Office continues to support the journey of recovery by presenting Personal Stories. Suicide Prevention If you are thinking about suicide, please call: 1-800-273-8255 Essential Links Get Help Treatment Prevention Crisis Services For SAMH Providers Program Information Events No events scheduled. Some files on this page may require free Adobe Reader. Download this software by clicking the link below Home ACCESS Florida Food, Medical & Cash Florida Abuse Hotline News & Events Contact Us Privacy Statement Accessibility Home Services Abuse Hotline ACCESS Florida Adoption Adult Protective Services Background Screening Child Care Child Welfare Children's Legal Services Community-Based Care Deaf and Hard-of-Hearing Disability or LEP Services Domestic Violence Foster Care Homelessness Human Trafficking Independent Living Services Interstate Compact for the Placement of Children Mental Health Public Benefits Integrity Refugee Services Substance Abuse General Information About Us News & Events Contact Us Back to the Top Connect with Us Facebook Twitter YouTube Blog Sign Up for Florida Dept of Children & Families Email Alerts Stay informed Sign Up for Updates E-Mail Address * Email address description           ©2014 Florida Department of Children & Families. All Rights Reserved.
